description: From Middle English misspeken, mispeken, mysspeken, from Old English *misspecan, missprecan (“to murmur”), equivalent to mis- +‎ speak.

verbs.description: misspeak (third-person singular simple present misspeaks, present participle misspeaking, simple past misspoke, past participle misspoken)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive, chiefly US) To fail to pronounce, utter, or speak correctly.
examples: Either I misspoke or you misheard.

entries.meaning: (intransitive, obsolete) To speak insultingly or disrespectfully.
